 Program: The opportunity to work with faculty, staff and other student leaders to advance the Bren School’s outreach and recruitment goals; The opportunity to strengthen your skills with public speaking, program and event planning, and teamwork and leadership skills; Work experience to add to your resumé; A quarterly stipend will be provided (TBD, based on 2008-09 final budget allocation). Minimum qualifications and requirements: Must have completed at least one year as a Bren School major (ICS, CSE, CSE or Informatics) Sophomore-level or junior standing by fall 2008 2.5 Minimum GPA Ability to effectively communicate your Bren School and Anteater pride to others Professional work habits (dependable, reliable, team player, willingness to learn) Willingness to perform student ambassador duties for fall, winter and spring quarters 2008-09; Willingness to demonstrate professional standards of language, behavior and dress (a Bren School t-shirt will be provided) at all times during assigned ambassador visits and outreach activities. Ambassador Responsibilities: Attend trainings and weekly meetings to assist with ambassador assignments, including planning, scheduling and hosting outreach events* (listed below); reviewing marketing materials; providing School and campus information to prospective applicants and their families by phone, electronic and in-person meetings. Develop working relationships with 3-4 feeder high schools or community colleges Help to develop a 15-20 minute Bren School presentation for K-12 audience Deliver at least 3 presentations quarterly to K-12 audiences (individually or in group format). SAO will provide mileage reimbursement for travel to local schools. Participate in assigned outreach activities, events* and tasks Communicate and work closely with SAO undergraduate counselors to ensure that all information being conveyed to the general community is accurate, consistent and reflective of Bren School outreach goals. *Outreach Events (some of these may change): FALL Welcome Week events ICS Preview Day (with Admissions) Faculty Forum for Community College Representatives WINTER High School Teachers Conference Bren ICS visit days for freshmen admits SPRING Stay-Over Experience for Freshmen/Transfer Admits Celebrate UCI Transfer Scholars Day Lunch for graduating seniors with Dean and ADSA More Undergraduate Contact Academic advising Course updates Academic year plan ICS majors Double major 2nd baccalaureate ICS minors Petitions Policies Academic honesty Academic standing Add, drop, & change options Change of Major Concurrent Enrollment Coursework outside UCI CS 199 / IN4MATX 199 Grade policy ICS Credit by Exam Laptop & computer use Withdrawal/Readmission Graduation ICS student life Upcoming events Computing support Title IX Resources Newly Admitted to ICS Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences University of California, Irvine 6210 Donald Bren Hall Irvine, CA 92697-3425 UCI Homepage UCI Directory Faculty & Staff ICS Intranet Kay Family Foundation Lab Facilities News Events Map & Directions Employment Safety Procedures Privacy Policy Apply Contact Gift © UCI Donald Bren School of Information & Computer Sciences ➤